title: Bobcats dominate Lyons in final home game
text: Bobcats dominate Lyons in final home game Trail-Gazette staff Posted: 10/24/2015 07:48:01 PM MDT The Estes Park High School football team celebrated its seniors final home game of the season with a 40-12 victory over Lyons on Friday night. Senior safety kicked things off early in the first quarter, intercepting a Lyons pass. Bobcat junior Caden Brown then ran in a touchdown from 42 yards out. Later in the second quarter, Estes Park junior quarterback Jordan Duemig threw a touchdown pass to senior wide receiver Logan Kittler. The Bobcats led 12-0 with 5:44 to go in the first half. Following a three-and-out by Lyons, Duemig connected with senior receiver Joseph Coleson for a TD. Tanner Stark booted the extra point, and the Bobcats led 19-0 heading into halftime. The Lions managed to find the end zone, but Estes answered. Following an interception by senior cornerback Evan Ginter, senior receiver Izzy Libby sprinted 63 yards for a touchdown. Stark's point after gave Estes Park a 26-6 lead. The Bobcat lead inflated, later on, when Woodard scored again. Stark's extra point made it 33-6. Lyons added a touchdown, and Bobcat senior running back Sam Addison scampered for 76 yards to cap off the night. Stark added the extra point, and Estes claimed the victory, 40-12. The Bobcats play the final game of the season 1 p.m. Saturday, Oct. 31 at Platte Canyon. Advertisement
